文献中的介绍: These findings suggest that transfer cells play a role in defense of filial seeds from attack by pathogens as well as in uptake of nutrients from the mother cells.

In flowering plants, the shoot apical meristem (SAM) is ultimately responsible for post-embryonic development of the primary shoot architecture. However, lateral meristems also play an important role in determining the final morphology of the above-ground part of plants.
